Here's a comprehensive list of CI/CD components and concepts, covering the full pipeline across tools and stages.
Core Pipeline Concepts
Fundamentals

Continuous Integration (CI) — frequent code merges + automated build/test
Continuous Delivery (CD) — automated release to staging, manual prod approval
Continuous Deployment (CD) — fully automated to production
Pipeline — defined sequence of automated stages
Pipeline as Code — pipeline defined in version-controlled files
Stages / Jobs / Steps / Tasks
Workflow / Pipeline definition
Triggers (push, PR, tag, schedule/cron, manual, webhook, API)
Runners / Agents / Executors
Artifacts — build outputs passed between stages
Caching — speed up dependency installs/builds

